This paper involves the analysis of social media data related to the US presidential election, which falls under the category of social media analytics. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves data analysis and statistics, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering and Data Analytics) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves natural language processing and sentiment analysis, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
